`user_id='javi_test'`. To restore default weights (use global):
```sql
DELETE FROM objective_weights WHERE user_id = 'javi_test';
```
(Solver's `get_objective_weights` falls back to `user_id='global'` when
user-specific returns empty — verified in R4 baseline fetch behavior.)

To flip again with different values, re-run `/tmp/r5_weight_flip.sql`
with modified coefficient values. The SQL is idempotent (`DELETE` +
`INSERT`).

